'''Interfolio''' is an academic faculty management software and higher education technology company based in Washington, D.C.<ref>{{cite web|title=Interfolio ByCommittee - Tips for Administrators {{!}} Faculty Administrative Services|url=http://facultyadmin.yale.edu/reappointments-promotions/interfolio-bycommittee-tips-administrators|publisher=[[Yale University]]|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Interfolio : References & Letters of Recommendation - Brandeis University|url=http://www.brandeis.edu/hiatt/howto/interfolio.html|publisher=[[Brandeis University]]|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Interfolio services overview|url=http://www.dartmouth.edu/prehealth/applying/evaluation_letters/interfolio.html|publisher=[[Dartmouth College]]|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=en}}</ref> The company provides software to assist shared governance processes and faculty activity tracking tools to assist with institutional accreditation and reporting.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cornell Career Services: Credentials Service|url=http://www.career.cornell.edu/resources/credential-service.cfm|publisher=[[Cornell University]]|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Recommendation Service - Health Professions and Prelaw Center - Indiana University - University Division|url=http://www.hpplc.indiana.edu/rs.shtml|publisher=[[Indiana University]]|accessdate=14 February 2017}}</ref> In January 2016, the company acquired $12 million in investor funding.<ref>{{cite web|title=Interfolio Raises $12M Series A Round to Expand Higher Education Human Resources Platform (EdSurge News)|url=https://www.edsurge.com/news/2016-01-11-interfolio-raises-12m-series-a-round-to-expand-higher-education-human-resources-platform|publisher=[[EdSurge]]|accessdate=14 February 2017}}</ref>
==Foundation and services==
Interfolio was founded by Georgetown University senior Steve Goldenberg in 1999.<ref>{{cite web|title=Higher-ed platform Interfolio raising Series B, hiring|url=http://www.elevationdcmedia.com/innovationnews/interfolio_04102014.aspx|publisher=Elevation DC Media|accessdate=14 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Street meets suit: Menswear revolution creates go-anywhere clothes|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/sf/style/2014/10/17/mens-fashion-street-meets-suit/|accessdate=14 February 2017|work=[[Washington Post]]}}</ref> Interfolio’s services represents a complete faculty lifecycle and information system. Interfolio was created to streamline the college application process for academic jobs by providing an online portfolio and application system. Principal Interfolio services includes Dossier, a service for collecting, curating, and delivering academic materials to scholarly opportunities.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Professor Is In: Is it a Mistake to Use a Dossier Service?|url=https://chroniclevitae.com/news/692-the-professor-is-in-is-it-a-mistake-to-use-a-dossier-service|publisher=Vitae|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=en}}</ref> Interfolio based a module for faculty information that includes a workflow and evaluation suite, as well as a tool for faculty activity reporting.<ref>{{cite news|title=Faculty Workflow Tech Company Interfolio Acquires DATA180 (EdSurge News)|url=https://www.edsurge.com/news/2017-01-17-faculty-workflow-tech-company-interfolio-acquires-data180|accessdate=14 February 2017|work=[[EdSurge]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Interfolio Acquires DATA180 to Improve Faculty Activity Reporting -- Campus Technology|url=https://campustechnology.com/articles/2017/01/18/interfolio-acquires-data180-to-improve-faculty-activity-reporting.aspx|publisher=Campus Technology|accessdate=14 February 2017|language=en}}</ref>
