The '''University Act''' was enacted by the [[Legislative Assembly of British Columbia]] to establish degree-granting [[university|universities]] for [[British Columbia]]. The first University Act was passed in 1890, which act continues in force and defines the first Convocation of The University of British Columbia. A subsequent Act was passed in 1908 (in conjunction with the University Endowment Act of 1907). Under this new statute, the governance of the [[University of British Columbia]] was clarified.
